newsitem.title: UK: NWE gasoline falls back with gas oil.
newsitem.headline: NWE gasoline falls back with gas oil.

text.p: NWE gasoline fell back with IPE gas oil on Monday in limited trade.
Prompt eurograde barges lost some eight dollars on the day with offers in late talk around $205 a tonne fob ARA. Trade was mainly at higher levels between $208 to $208.50 a tonne.
Traders said that run cuts had started in the Mediterranean and in Europe should help support prices.
"It doesn't look too healthy at the moment but the inventory in Europe is not very high and prices should bounce back soon. The States will lead the price revival," one trader said.
April swaps traded earlier from a high of $212 to a low of $209 a tonne and was offered down to $208.
